<br>
The first step towards focus items was to make the first wave of focus items Mage summons. Fortunately for us, all of the focus item summons are found in a relatively easy place to find: The Bazaar. This allowed for fast distribution for people to try out, and also allowed for easy changes.<br>
<br>
A few months later they retroactively added focus effects to existing items. Examples include the Obulus Death Shroud, Robe of the Oracle, Drachnid Thyxl, etc.<br>
<br>
How does this affect Mages? With little to no effort, we mages can substantially increase our offensive and defensive power, simply by summoning a couple trinkets for us to wear. And where our summons fail, there are droppable items to fill the gap. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ualucard101.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alucard101</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#333333>(9/21/02 4:16:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=335.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   focus.....</span><hr size=1> it's not too hard to get focus... <br>
